    java.io.Serializable

    public class DocumentNotFoundException
extends java.io.IOException
    An exception that indicates that an attempt to read an unreadable document occurred.

        Constructs an DocumentNotFoundException with the specified cause and a detail message of (cause==null ? null : cause.toString()) (which typically contains the class and detail message of cause). This constructor is useful for IO exceptions that are little more than wrappers for other throwables.
        Parameters:
